<h1 class="title">Write your docs with Ruby on Rails</h1>

<p class="subtitle" data-controller="typewriter" data-typewriter-phrases-value='[ "Power of Rails", "Finesse of Hotwire", "Speed of Jekyll", "Awe of Docusaurus" ]'>
  Unleash the&ensp;<span class="typewriter" data-typewriter-target="typewrite">Power of Rails</span>&ensp;with HotDocs
</p>

<%= image_tag "/hotdocs.svg", class: "logo", alt: "TODO", size: "160x160" %>

<div class="action">
  <%= link_to "Get started", quickstart_path, class: "action__button" %>
</div>

<div class="benefits">
  <h2>HotDocs is a set of optimized Rails components &amp; tools for writing docs</h2>

  <div class="benefits__cards">
    <div class="benefits__card">
      <p class="benefits__card-title">It's just Rails</p>

      <p>Do you need the database? Or want to reuse code? What about Hotwire? Yes, yes, and yes! You'll feel at home.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefits__card">
      <p class="benefits__card-title">Write the docs</p>

      <p>HotDocs covers all your bases, you only need to author the content. Markdown support (and plugins) coming soon.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="benefits__card">
      <p class="benefits__card-title">Static export 🔜</p>

      <p>Export Html and Css for speed while allowing islands of dynamic Js that can interact with your backend.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

